-- BHP May Pull Out of Accord With Gillard on Mining Tax, Australian Reports
-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 2010-10-19T19:51:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/bhp-may-pull-out-of-accord-with-gillard-on-mining-tax-australian-reports.html
BHP Billiton Ltd. may drop an
agreement with Australia’s government that covers a mining tax
after a minister said any future increases in state royalties
couldn’t be offset by cuts to the tax, the Australian reported,
citing an unidentified person familiar with the matter.  The accord isn’t likely to break “imminently,” the
newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  